From: Eliza Phase E <noreply@elizaos.dev>
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] llama.cpp: add LLAMA_BUILD_OMNIVOICE option (no-op until vendor tree lands)
Date: 2026-05-12

Adds an opt-in CMake option that will (once patch 0002 vendors the
tree under `tools/omnivoice/`) wire the merged omnivoice subtree into
the canonical llama.cpp build.

Default OFF so existing llama.cpp consumers see no change. When ON,
the build currently fails fast with an actionable error message — the
flag exists, but the actual subtree has not landed yet (that's patch
0002). This makes the flag-introduction patch safe to land first
without breaking ON builds with a silent missing-directory error.

---
 CMakeLists.txt | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -109,6 +109,15 @@ option(LLAMA_BUILD_EXAMPLES "llama: build examples"       ${LLAMA_STANDALONE})
 option(LLAMA_BUILD_SERVER   "llama: build server example" ${LLAMA_STANDALONE})
 option(LLAMA_TOOLS_INSTALL  "llama: install tools"        ${LLAMA_TOOLS_INSTALL_DEFAULT})
 option(LLAMA_TESTS_INSTALL  "llama: install tests"        ON)
+
+# omnivoice.cpp merged subtree: opt-in. When enabled, tools/omnivoice/
+# is compiled against the same GGML + backend selection as the rest of
+# llama.cpp, producing the libomnivoice shared library (when
+# OMNIVOICE_SHARED is also set) and the omnivoice-tts / omnivoice-codec
+# CLI tools. Default OFF so stock llama.cpp consumers see no change.
+# NOTE: until patch 0002 vendors tools/omnivoice/, enabling this flag
+# is a hard error — see the guard near the bottom of this file.
+option(LLAMA_BUILD_OMNIVOICE "Build the merged omnivoice TTS subtree" OFF)
+option(OMNIVOICE_SHARED      "Build libomnivoice for ABI consumers" OFF)

 # 3rd party libs
 option(LLAMA_OPENSSL    "llama: use openssl to support HTTPS" ON)
@@ -213,3 +222,10 @@ if (LLAMA_BUILD_COMMON AND LLAMA_BUILD_TOOLS)
     add_subdirectory(tools)
 endif()

+if (LLAMA_BUILD_OMNIVOICE)
+    if (NOT EXISTS "${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/tools/omnivoice/CMakeLists.txt")
+        message(FATAL_ERROR
+            "LLAMA_BUILD_OMNIVOICE=ON but OMNIVOICE_VENDOR_DIR not yet wired (patch 0002). "
+            "Vendor tools/omnivoice/ from packages/inference/omnivoice.cpp first, then re-run cmake.")
+    endif()
+    add_subdirectory(tools/omnivoice)
+endif()
